    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p><b><h>Problem Statement:</h></b></p>\nThere is a famous Buddhist monastery on the top of a mountain. \n</br>There are<b> N</b> stairs from ground to reach the monastery. it\u2019s a very tuff trail for the pilgrims so there is another way to reach the monastery is by lift. \n</br>A group of pilgrims wishes to visit the monastery. \n</br>Each time a pilgrim can either climb <b>1 or M </b>no. of steps. \n</br>Every pilgrims wants to climb those stairs in unique way so the no. of different ways to climb to the top of the stairs is the no. of pilgrims allowed to climb. \n</br>Rest of the pilgrims have to go by the lift. \n</br>Ticket charges to go by the stairs is <b>Rs. X </b>per visitor and to go by the lift is <b>Rs. Y</b> per visitor to reach monastery.\n</br> What will be minimum amount of money to be required to visit monastery for all pilgrims?\n</br>\n</br>\n<b>NOTE</b>:-It is necessary for every pilgrim to visit monastery.\n</br></br>\n<p><b><h>Input Format</h></b></p>\nFirst line of the input has an integer\u00a0T.\u00a0\n</br>Each test case contains an integer\u00a0N (number of stairs) and P (number of pilgrims) and M (No of step Jump) separated by space. \n</br>The next line will contain the ticket prices for both stairs and lift all are separated by space.\n</br></br>\n<p><b><h>Output Format</h></b></p>\u00a0\nFor each test case, print minimum  amount of money required  to reach the monastery in a new line.\n</br></br>\n<p><b><h>Constraints:</h></b></p>\n<ul>\n<p><b>SubTask#1</b></p>\n1<=T<=10^5\n</br>1<=N<=10^6\n</br>1<=P<=10^6\n</br>1<=M<=25\n</br>1<=X,Y<=10^5\n</br></br>\n<p><b>SubTask#2</b></p>\nOriginal Constraints..\n</br>\n</br>\n<p><b>SubTask#3</b></p>\nOriginal Constraints..\n</ul>\n</br></br>\n<p><b><h>Sample Input:</h></b></p>\n1\n</br>48 50 1\n</br>3 10\n</br></br></br>\n<p><b><h>Sample Output:</h></b></p>\n493\n</br></br>\n<p><b><h>Explanation:</h></b></p>\n Number of test case is 1.\n          </br>and N=48 & P=50 & M=1\n          </br>and ticket price of stairs is 3 and for lift is 10.\n</br>Since, cost to climb by stairs and by lift combined is 493. ",
